abstract: Seven Democratic presidential candidates will take the stage in Los Angeles on Thursday in the party's sixth debate of the nominating contest for the November 2020 U.S. election.
snippet: Seven Democratic presidential candidates will take the stage in Los Angeles on Thursday in the party's sixth debate of the nominating contest for the November 2020 U.S. election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Seven Democratic presidential candidates will take the stage in Los Angeles on Thursday in the party's sixth debate of the nominating contest for the November 2020 U.S. election.
headline_main: Live From Los Angeles: Three Things to Watch in the Democratic Presidential Debate
headline_print_headline: Live From Los Angeles: Three Things to Watch in the Democratic Presidential Debate

abstract: This month’s constructor spotlight shines on Damon Gulczynski.
snippet: This month’s constructor spotlight shines on Damon Gulczynski.
lead_paragraph: I currently live in Washington, D.C., but I like to represent my hometown, University Place, Wash., which, ironically, has never been home to a university.

abstract: Do you need something to look forward to over the holidays? At 500-plus pages, these novels are worth the extra space in your luggage or megabytes on your device.

lead_paragraph: Escape can be a slippery concept. You buy a ticket or fill your tank, enlist a friend to feed your cats and exit everyday life with great fanfare. “See you in 2020,” you say to co-workers, bus drivers and the neighbor you passed over for cat-sitting because he snoops.

abstract: Before he died, my father never talked about his time in the military. Now I’m trying to put the pieces together using the clues he left behind.
snippet: Before he died, my father never talked about his time in the military. Now I’m trying to put the pieces together using the clues he left behind.
lead_paragraph: I nestled into bed with a paperback copy of “The Things They Carried,” by Tim O’Brien. It had belonged to my dad. He thought the 1990 collection of short stories was the most realistic portrayal of the Vietnam War he had ever read. My father, Jack Reilly, died five years ago, and this book was one of the pieces I had left of him.

abstract: The 1992 feminist sensation “Women Who Run With the Wolves” has returned, as a new generation of artists embrace women’s bodies in all their hormonal, bloody glory.
snippet: The 1992 feminist sensation “Women Who Run With the Wolves” has returned, as a new generation of artists embrace women’s bodies in all their hormonal, bloody glory.
lead_paragraph: I first spied the book last spring, in the lap of a vaguely witchy young woman pinched between two men on the subway. Soon the book disappeared into a woven bag, her shoulder brushed against mine, and it was as if she had initiated me into a secret club. After that, I saw the book everywhere: in the hands of a tattooed solo diner while she ate a game bird in a Texas restaurant; nestled with the new releases on female rage in a Brooklyn bookstore; on Lana Del Rey’s Instagram.
